# Todo List for Website Development

## General
- [ ] Define the purpose and goals of the website
- [ ] Research and identify target audience
- [ ] Create a project timeline and milestones

## Design
- [ ] Create wireframes for each page
- [ ] Design the user interface (UI)
- [ ] Design the user experience (UX)
- [ ] Create a style guide (colors, fonts, etc.)
- [ ] Design responsive layouts for mobile and desktop

## Development
### Frontend
- [ ] Set up the project structure
- [ ] Implement HTML structure for each page
- [ ] Add CSS for styling
- [ ] Implement JavaScript for interactivity
- [ ] Ensure cross-browser compatibility
- [ ] Optimize images and media

### Backend
- [ ] Set up the server environment
- [ ] Implement database schema
- [ ] Develop API endpoints
- [ ] Implement user authentication and authorization
- [ ] Set up email services (if needed)

## Content
- [ ] Write copy for each page
- [ ] Create and optimize images and media
- [ ] Implement SEO best practices
- [ ] Create a blog or news section (if needed)

## Testing
- [ ] Perform unit testing
- [ ] Perform integration testing
- [ ] Perform user acceptance testing (UAT)
- [ ] Test for accessibility
- [ ] Test for performance and optimization

## Deployment
- [ ] Choose a hosting provider
- [ ] Set up domain and DNS
- [ ] Deploy the website
- [ ] Set up SSL certificate
- [ ] Implement backup and recovery plan

## Maintenance
- [ ] Set up monitoring and analytics
- [ ] Plan for regular updates and maintenance
- [ ] Create a support plan for users

## Marketing
- [ ] Develop a marketing strategy
- [ ] Set up social media profiles
- [ ] Create a content marketing plan
- [ ] Implement email marketing campaigns
- [ ] Plan for SEO and SEM

## Legal
- [ ] Create terms of service and privacy policy
- [ ] Ensure compliance with data protection regulations (e.g., GDPR)
- [ ] Obtain necessary licenses and permissions

## Feedback
- [ ] Collect user feedback
- [ ] Implement improvements based on feedback
- [ ] Continuously monitor and improve the website